(RecordsStashed (1 1261 [(4itr ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Constraint [The foundational principle of the whole schema design, stated with maximum force and repeatedly missed by agents: EVERYTHING is a serializable data object, the MACRO most of all. A macro is NOT parsing code that turns text into opaque behavior - it is a DATA OBJECT with a name, a position, a pattern, and a template, where the pattern and template are themselves data trees, not text with placeholder sigils. Macros are ASSEMBLED FIRST into assembled-schema data, then that assembled data is read to obtain the usable macro - so macros can be PRE-ASSEMBLED, serialized, and loaded as data. Reading any schema means loading the pre-assembled macro data and interpreting the schema-data against it to produce more assembled data. The ONLY code is one tiny generic interpreter over data; there is no per-macro bespoke parsing. The test of understanding: if you cannot serialize and deserialize a thing, you have not built it as data - every single thing round-trips through NOTA text and rkyv bytes, macros included. The current engine VIOLATES this: its macro expansion builds a string from the template and re-parses it, which is exactly the parse-then-black-magic slop the psyche rejects.] Maximum VeryHigh Zero [])) (7sx6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [|Every component has exactly two contracts and no more: signal-<component> (ordinary working signal) and meta-signal-<component> (meta policy signal) — there is no third contract, no owner-signal split, no engine-management split.|] Maximum VeryHigh Zero [])) (hp9n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Constraint [The repos directory must remain untracked; it is a local symlink index, and tracking it would turn repository coordination into circus-level churn.] Maximum High Zero [])) (b1vi ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Principle [Clients translate NOTA text into binary 