s-local AI model prefetch, hash mining, builds, and evaluations must run on Prometheus or the designated AI node that already holds the model files; agents must not trigger large model downloads or model builds on other computers. *capacity planning*] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (3d5z ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Constraint [The triad engine separation is strict and absolute: the SEMA engine owns ALL database and durable-state code, the Nexus engine owns ALL decision-making, and the Signal engine owns ALL communication. A component daemon must contain NO database boilerplate, NO decision-making, and NO communication code outside its respective engine — every such concern lives in its engine and nowhere else.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (4wt3 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Principle [The domain vocabulary is a variable-depth tree: dense branches such as software nest a third tier of variants for fine subjects, while sparse life domains stay two-tier; tree depth tracks intent density] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (6grf ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Decision [Schema is a specialized NOTA dialect built on structural macro nodes — a schema file is full NOTA, not a separate language lowered into NOTA.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (beaj ([(Technology (Software (Observability Tracing)))] Constraint [|There is no daemon-side printline. There shouldn't be. The daemon observes through its own tracing and logging mechanism — the typed schema-defined trace interface and any future logging surface. Stderr printline statements as fallback for in-band trace errors violate the typed-data-strings-only-at-display rule (Spirit 1490 Maximum) and are forbidden. This elevates and restates Spirit 1505 with Maximum certainty.|] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (cjrl ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Principle [Secrets always land in the most secure place available. In the user session that is gopass, which is git-backed and encrypted. For cluster deployment that is SOPS-nix, encrypted at rest in the repository and decrypted only on the target host at activation. Move a secret between stores by piping ciphertext to ciphertext, never through a visible intermediate.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (o7zt ([(Language Rhetoric)] Correction [When communicating with the psyche, agents must NEVER lead with or show a bare opaque identifier — a bead id, a Spirit record number, a content hash, a jj change id, a commit short-id. The human cannot decode these in their head and has no database access. ALWAYS lead with a short plain-language description of what the thing is or what it decided; the identifier is at most a quiet trailing reference in chat, and in reports a findable reference that is ALWAYS paired with a description. This applies to Spirit record numbers exactly as to bead hashes: a bare record number means nothing to the psyche without saying what it decided. Agents keep violating this, so the rule must be made prominent in the reporting and beads skills, not left only in the compact contract. Do not address the human as if they were a peer machine with query access.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (r2x2 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Decision [Agents commit the ENTIRE working copy, never path-scoped. In the shared jj working copy, path-scoped commits leave other agents changes undrained, letting two agents create sibling commits off the same base — the fork that strands work off-main and can orphan files. Committing everything drains the shared working copy and serializes agents through the jj working-copy lock, giving linear history; whoever commits sweeps in all in-flight work so nothing is orphaned. Commits become multi-lane, which is accepted. Supersedes the path-selective do-not-commit-other-lanes-files rule; skills/jj.md and the AGENTS.md path-selective note need updating to match.] VeryHigh VeryHigh Zero [])) (20hv ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [Landed means on main. Work on a branch has no material existence — it is a concept until an operator integrates it to main. Agents must never report pushed or branch-resident work as landed or done; state it as pushed to branch X awaiting operator integration, and reserve landed and done for work that is on main. Claiming branch work as landed is a false status report, and it damaged multi-agent coordination when other agents acted on the claim and chased a change that was never on main.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (6cfr ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Decision [|The separate Assembled Schema (Asschema) IR is removed; the resolution it performed (inline-declaration hoisting, visibility, ordering, symbol paths) lives as methods on schema-in-rust types used during the lower step, and the emitter does only Rust projection, not schema semantics.|] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (6x2k ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Principle [Use the github remote url form for flake and repository references, both in committed flake inputs and in nix build or nix run commands. Commit and push changes first, then build from the remote, so the build is reproducible, machine-independent, and free of silent uncommitted state. Never build or deploy from a local path checkout or a git-file reference: it is non-reproducible bad form. If a build needs a not-yet-pushed change, push it rather than pointing the build at the dirty local checkout. A local path or override-input is only for throwaway local iteration, never for anything that deploys or lands.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (813q ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Decision [|The canonical pipeline: authored schema (NOTA) deserializes via the structural-macro-node codec directly into schema-in-rust (typed, rkyv-serializable, canonical round-trip), which then lowers into Rust interface code.|] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (8bwo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Every component exposes its two contracts, the working signal and the meta policy signal, as two thin CLI clients: the working client named after the component and the meta client prefixed meta-. This is one extracted pattern applied across all components with minimal per-component hand-coding, not re-implemented per component. Spirit spirit and meta-spirit are the first instance.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (a71r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|Every component engine in the workspace triad architecture defines and uses its Signal, Nexus, and SEMA interfaces in schema, and conducts core logic through schema-emitted traits whose methods take and return root types of the concerned interfaces — adapting Spirit 1326 (spirit-engine-specific) to the workspace-wide component-triad pattern. The trait surface is uniform across components; each component's runtime is a composition of schema-emitted trait implementations.|] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (a9sq ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|The rkyv binary form is the SINGLE encoded representation that lives in BOTH the database (sema body at rest) AND on the wire (signal movement between clients). One byte layout, two homes. NOTA is the text-readable projection emitted at CLI read time or for human inspection. Same AssembledSchema reads bytes in both contexts; same encoded form survives storage and transport.|] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (eny6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Every statement written into an intent or essence surface — ESSENCE.md, workspace INTENT.md, a per-repo INTENT.md — must be anchored in an actual Spirit intent record, verified against the store, not invented or inferred. These files are syntheses of recorded intent; a claim with no Spirit record behind it does not belong, or the intent is recorded first.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (hnpo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [MetaSignal is the canonical name for the policy and authority contract; OwnerSignal is deprecated. Every component policy contract is named meta-signal then component uniformly, including ones whose repos are absent or still owner-signal-prefixed today — meta-signal-persona, meta-signal-criome, and meta-signal-agent are born meta-signal, never owner-signal. This confirms and generalizes record r9qy from its specific repo rename list to the universal naming principle, and answers system-designer report 77 decision 1: from-scratch policy contracts are born meta-signal.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (j4r1 ([(Technology (Software (Operations ConfigurationManagement)))] Constraint [agents do not install software statefully in this workspace: no pip installs, persistent virtualenvs, or downloaded toolchains in the home directory. Use ephemeral nix shell or nix run only, matching the workspace ephemeral and declarative Nix ethos] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (nqsb ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Every repository must have an INTENT.md, and it is the FIRST file to create for a repo — the most important file, answering: what is this repository for? A repo's INTENT.md holds the most important AND ONLY the most important design intent and design constraints that concern that project; it is curated and distilled to the essential, not an accumulation of everything. Isolating the most important design constraints into each repo's INTENT.md is a priority, and Psyche reports explaining a repo should be based on its reviewed/curated INTENT.md. Per psyche 2026-06-04.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (nu76 ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Constraint [A major first-digit version bump toward 1.0 and beyond requires explicit psyche authorization; agents may propose a major bump but the psyche gives the go.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (op4b ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [Agents must NOT create new GitHub repositories for architectural breaks, experiments, mockups, repros, or design passes. That work belongs on feature branches in worktrees under the existing repo. The skill major-break-via-new-repo is retired — it caused a proliferation of throwaway repos such as design-deep-spirit-2026-05-26, design-nota-from-schema, signal-frame-mockup-stable-caller-id-1, kameo-supervised-shutdown-repro, and signal-frame-worktrees, plus -next repos never renamed back to canonical so spirit-next is now just a symlink to spirit. The design-prefixed-repo guidance in double-implementation-strategy is retired with it. Default is always feature-development branches and worktrees. New repositories are created only on explicit psyche authority. Per psyche 2026-06-07.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (pr61 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Principle [Domain tree depth is proportional to intent density, not a structural exception: Software nests deeper because it holds far more, while sparse Hardware stays one level.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (vfjw ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Clarification [|NOTA strings come EXCLUSIVELY from bracket forms - the canonical [text] form for ordinary strings and the [|text\|] form for strings containing brackets (escape-free zone). Quotation marks do NOT form string types in NOTA. Safe NOTA is free of unescaped quotation marks; quotation marks are strongly disfavored as a string syntax. The earlier record 690 framed this as authoring preference; this clarification strengthens it to a structural rule about the NOTA format itself: brackets ARE the string form. Implementations that accept double-quoted strings as input (legacy lojix-cli, possibly historical NOTA reader code) are non-canonical legacy and slated for removal. Test imperative: latest NOTA must behave per this rule; emitter and parser audited; legacy quotation-string handling, if any, marked for retirement. *lexical analysis*|] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (xo9g ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Decision [Cross-tree domain relations are symmetric equivalence only — synonyms that retrieve together both ways. Directional subsumption between domains is dropped because the nested tree and scope-prefix matching already carry all hierarchy.] VeryHigh High Zero [])) (0fs6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [owner-signal-persona is the deprecated OwnerSignal form and should become meta-signal-persona, and signal-engine-management is an off-pattern name that should fold into the signal-persona / meta-signal-persona pair.] VeryHigh Medium Zero [])) (7c71 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture))) (Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Principle [A programming language is, in essence, a set of structural macros — constructors that take a typed, counted set of objects, with Rust's struct, enum, fn, impl, and generics included and every language likewise. Conventional languages freeze that macro set inside the compiler, making it closed. This approach instead treats the macro set as data, so the language becomes infinitely extensible — new constructs are added as data rather than compiler changes — and far easier for an LLM to read, write, and reason about, because the language's own constructs are uniform typed data in the schema-NOTA-rkyv substrate.] VeryHigh Medium Zero [schema-next nota-next])) (rg2i ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Decision [|Version magnitude follows the digits: a small change bumps the patch digit (0.3.0 to 0.3.1) and a functionality change such as privacy work bumps the minor digit (0.3 to 0.4).|] VeryHigh Medium Zero [])) (rtrf ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [|For persona specifically: signal-persona exists and is canonical and correct (NOT a retired compatibility shim, despite its README's false label); meta-signal-persona is currently missing and should be created.|] VeryHigh Medium Zero [])) (nfje ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [Bare signal-persona references in docs are correct and must NOT be migrated away.] VeryHigh Low Zero [])) (1ykl ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [ESSENCE.md holds only the universal workspace essence — how agents behave across every role and repo. It carries nothing role-specific, repo-specific, or technically-specific: no two-roles framing, no Rust-module, daemon-edge, trace-edge, or strings-at-the-edge detail. Workspace INTENT.md is general workspace rules. Repo-specific essence and intent live in the per-repo INTENT.md, not the workspace files; provenance references are stripped.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (26e7 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [The schema-derived component triad is NOT one daemon schema file with Signal Nexus and SEMA sections. A component is at least three separate plane schema files. The Signal wire contract lives in the contract repos and stays wire-only. The Nexus and SEMA plane schemas are separate schema files INSIDE the component daemon crate — for example cloud/schema/nexus.schema and cloud/schema/sema.schema — each declaring its own imports exports input output and namespace and each importing the wire-contract Signal IO. Plane schemas are NOT separate crates and NOT separate repos; per-plane crate split is not the triad shape. The daemon runtime composition imports and connects the separate plane schemas rather than embedding Nexus and SEMA sections inside the contract or inside a single all-in-one daemon schema.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (4728 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Correction [Operator-lane subagents must be treated as asynchronous side work: dispatch returns control to the main agent, and the main agent should keep working or answer new psyche prompts instead of blocking on subagent completion. Waiting for a subagent is only acceptable when explicitly requested or when the psyche is not waiting on the main agent for anything else.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (4r1d ([(Work Leadership)] Decision [videographer is a new main workspace role: video as craft covering filming and screen capture, editing, captioning, encoding, and publishing preparation. It parallels the poet craft role. The psyche created it and assigned it to the Claude session that handled the video captions research. Lock file orchestrate/videographer.lock, reports under reports/videographer/] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (7hrd ([(Technology (Software Data))] Correction [|Working orders - ephemeral task directives like create-a-report-and-test-it, dispatch-a-subagent-to-X, audit-Y-and-write-a-report, operator-integrate-these-branches - are NOT intent and must not be logged as Spirit records. The intent log holds only DURABLE psyche statements (Decision/Principle/Correction/Clarification/Constraint) that outlive any single task and guide future work. The test: would the record still be meaningful and guiding AFTER the task it refers to is done? If no, it is a working order and belongs in the session task list or beads, not Spirit. When a psyche prompt is a task directive, capture only the durable intent statements WITHIN it (the design decisions, principles, corrections), not the do-the-task part. Generalizes record 1090 (the 1088 over-capture by the operator). Per record 1091, a mis-logged working order is FLAGGED as a capture error, not deleted (append-only provenance). Manifest this test into skills/intent-log.md. *validation*|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (7y8w ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Principle [|NOTA's bracket-only string discipline makes a complete NOTA expression embedding-safe inside any host language whose string syntax uses double quotes - JSON, Rust string literals (including raw r-strings), Nix attribute values, YAML scalars, TOML strings, shell double-quote arguments, HTTP request bodies, database string columns, environment variable values, XML attributes - all without escaping NOTA's contents. The cycle: brackets are the NOTA string form, so NOTA never contains a double-quote; therefore any host language using double-quotes can carry a NOTA payload escape-free. Same principle that makes shell double-quotes the clean outer wrapper, scaled up: NOTA is the universal embedding-safe payload for structured data in string-carrying contexts. JSON-in-JSON requires escape cascades; NOTA-in-anything-with-doublequote-strings is escape-free. This is a load-bearing design property of NOTA, not an incidental side effect.|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (di1r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Correction [|jj commands must always use inline/headless flags (-m / --no-edit / --message=); NEVER invocations that spawn an editor for commit/describe/squash etc. AGENTS.md hard-override must encode this so sub-agents do not stall waiting for editor input|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (ejec ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Principle [avoid invoking nix store hash paths directly; use nix run, nix shell, or nix build --out-link with temporary symlinks] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (fosp ([(Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Correction [Sema-engine is the exclusive interface to the database. No component daemon may make direct redb calls — all durable database work goes through sema-engine, which owns the redb interaction. A daemon that opens redb and runs its own transactions directly is wrong, even as a pilot, and counts as a fake of the intended architecture. The schema-derived spirit pilot bypassed sema-engine with raw redb to keep its proof self-contained; that was a misunderstanding of sema-engine intended role as the database boundary. Components are dumb about storage and speak only sema-engine operations.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (g78b ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Correction [When the psyche says refresh intent, it means the agent should refresh its own context by reading recent Spirit intent records; it is not an instruction to edit repo INTENT.md or architecture files unless the psyche explicitly asks for file edits.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (hc0t ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Constraint [The assembled schema - the .asschema - is canonical NOTA ONLY: the round-trip form produced by AsschemaNotaWriter and parsed by AsschemaNotaReader. The hand-rolled human-readable line format - the one printing the word fixture then a name, identity, imports, macro_trace, and types written as newtype-name then the equals sign then the type, with indented lists - is FORBIDDEN and must never be produced again, whether named .asschema or .witness.txt. Even as a so-called readable witness it is rejected: delete it, do not rename it. Everything is data; the only assembled-schema representation is NOTA and rkyv. This applies record 1109 specifically to the assembled schema. The psyche stated this with maximum force after the format resurfaced repeatedly.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (hl1z ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [Schema defines data types ONLY - no effects, no fan-out targets, no effect tables. Effects are runtime dispatch / logic and have NO place in schema. The EffectTable + FanOutTargets + StorageDescriptor Feature variants that landed via the schema-crystallization arc were agent-hallucinated drift; they were never psyche-authorized. Schema stays in its lane: it declares data types.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (k2o1 ([(Technology (Software (Operations DependencyManagement)))] Correction [|Zero consumers does NOT mean a repo is dead. Some repos — notably the triad signal-component and meta-signal-component contract repos — are MEANT to be used; if a component is not yet depending on its standalone contract, the correct action is to START using it (adopt and wire it), NOT delete it. signal-spirit, signal-forge, signal-lojix and the like are intended working-signal contracts for their components, currently unadopted because components still emit their contracts in-repo — that is a migration gap, not a tombstone. A repository audit must distinguish intended-but-not-yet-adopted from genuinely-dead by understanding the intended component and triad architecture FIRST, before recommending any deletion. The system-designer 83 audit erred by listing intended-active contracts as deletions. Per psyche 2026-06-07.|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (k4i3 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Skills are tight self-contained teaching, not logs. Write each skill directly to its correct current state — never leave a correction or changelog banner narrating what changed. A skill cites nothing external: no report links, no Spirit record identifiers or numbers, no back-and-forth cross-reference indirection. Brevity is load-bearing — agents arrive already full of training, so bloated skills consume the very context they need to work and confuse more than they teach. Cut hard: state the rule and the why, drop redundancy, keep at most one example. The same restraint applies to reports — fewer and tighter.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (krez ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Correction [Work orders are not intent records] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (laim ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Decision [NOTA bare string atoms should allow a broad punctuation set. Comments require a double semicolon marker. A single semicolon is ordinary bare atom text. Typed String decoding rejects bracket-delimited strings when the decoded text is eligible for bare atom formatting. *lexical analysis*] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (p4sm ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Constraint [On primary — the workspace coordination repository — everyone always works on main directly: edit, commit, and push straight to main with the simple flow. No feature, next, wip, or push branches on primary, and no rebase-onto-main dances. The main-and-next branching model of record 2561 applies only to the code repositories under git, where operators own main and designers work on next; primary itself is everyone-on-main, always. Just commit and push to main on primary — it is simple.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (p6fx ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [Major engine version upgrades happen atomically in real time with no downtime. The workspace is a continuous runtime; component upgrades coordinate via Persona to swap versions without interrupting service.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (rvnf ([(Information Curation)] Correction [Agents must not respond to Spirit overcapture by avoiding Spirit entirely; the correct discipline is to apply the conservative capture gate and use Spirit only for explicit durable decisions, principles, corrections, clarifications, and constraints.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [spirit capture-gate])) (sjcy ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [CLIs are thin Signal clients] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (t4gd ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Principle [A daemon binary must compile with no NOTA code at all. NOTA encode/decode is a thin-CLI text-edge concern only; the daemon speaks binary/rkyv exclusively and must not pull nota-next into its compiled artifact. Component crates gate NOTA behind a nota-text feature that only the CLI binary enables, so the daemon build is NOTA-free. Pairs with signal being NOTA-free.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (vr32 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [NOTA structs are positional only — no field names in the wire form. The position of an object in a struct determines what it is, via the schema applied at read time. Designer 326 v2 violated this by tagging Schema/Channel/Namespace as head tags; tags are unnecessary because position already encodes meaning. The reader knows from context this is a schema file.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (yjik ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Clarification [Signal repositories carry only the signal schema for their wire vocabulary; non-signal schema for runtime planes, storage, provider effects, REST surfaces, or broader component behavior belongs in the runtime component or the appropriate schema/runtime repository, not in the signal repository.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (z6qu ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|The Nexus interface — verbs and objects declared in the nexus schema — is the engine's INTERNAL FEATURE INTERFACE, and its MAIN reason for existing is VISIBILITY of the engine's internal features. Every engine feature — any computation, any filtering or condition on results, any conditional write (conditional writing), any internal logic-feature — MUST be defined as a Nexus interface verb + object in the schema, so that every such operation has a typed internal interface AND the complete feature surface of the engine is visible in the nexus schema declaration. Internal features must not live as inline hand-written logic hidden from the schema; they are declared Nexus verbs/objects. The nexus schema is therefore the readable catalog of everything the engine can do internally. Per psyche 2026-06-05.|] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (zt1 ([(Information Curation)] Correction [Agents apply the conservative capture gate] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [spirit])) (zt2 ([(Information Documentation)] Correction [Agents apply the conservative capture gate] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [spirit capture-gate])) (zt3 ([(Information Curation)] Correction [Agents apply the conservative capture gate] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [])) (zt4 ([(Information Documentation)] Correction [Agents apply the conservative capture gate] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [capture-gate])) (i4ak ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl))) (Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [The reusable component version-control system is foundational to the whole meta-work and must support full distributed-version-control semantics over the typed database: branching, forking, 