erive) is OPT-IN per consumer. Every client needs the binary rkyv representation to talk to the daemon at all. Only DOUBLE clients (text + binary, e.g. the CLI) need the NOTA derive; binary-only clients (the daemon, future binary-only consumers) must NOT have NotaDecode/NotaEncode impls compiled in — for (a) leanness (daemon decoder cost / dependency closure) and (b) contract clarity (the daemon's wire shouldn't even ACCEPT NOTA text; the absence of NotaDecode at the compile boundary enforces this structurally). Same data types across consumers — what differs is the derive set, not the wire shape. Schema-rust-next's emitter must produce both forms from one .asschema. Wire byte-compatibility comes from the shared rkyv layout being identical regardless of whether NOTA derives are present. Mechanism research in report 430 (cargo feature on the contract crate + structural split of binary crates so feature unification does not merge daemon and CLI). Per psyche 2026-05-30.|] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (cws0 ([(Information Curation)] Decision [|Deployed Spirit can REMOVE intent records, superseding the append-only/flag-only constraint. Clean the log by removing (1) stale records superseded by a newer record/INTENT.md/skill that absorbs their substance, and (2) working orders that fail the after-the-task test. Every change needs a justifying psyche statement (a deletion is justified by e.g. a changed mind, no replacement arrow required); removal is psyche-authorized and conservative — when removability is uncertain, flag rather than remove, since over-removal beats under-removal.|] High VeryHigh Zero [spirit intent-log])) (el7z ([(Work Productivity)] Correction [|Do not block waiting for a subagent to return. The prime designer's parallel-subagent workflow (intent record 57) means the agent runs OTHER work — own thinking, additional tool calls, context reading, chat preparation — WHILE the subagent is in flight, not as a synchronous wait. When a subagent is dispatched, the dispatching agent continues productive work and only checks the subagent's result at a natural integration point. The harness pauses the conversation until tool calls return, but the agent should always have multiple tools in flight rather than dispatching one and waiting.|] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (hgvg ([(Information Documentation)] Principle [Reference intent records in prose markdown by quoting the description summary literally as bracketed text — the bracketed form IS the citation — not by the record number alone. Repetition reinforces intent: the number is an opaque address, the substance is what's load-bearing. Especially in psyche-facing reports, and wherever an intent is central to a document, quote it literally in a prominent place. Applies to all agents.] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (j6r4 ([(Technology (Software Data))] Principle [Spirit certainty follows an honest 8-level magnitude rubric. Maximum only for foundational invariants and hard overrides that are repeatedly ratified and stable. VeryHigh for ratified decisions clearly in force. High for solid decisions with minor open edges. Medium for working decisions and design directions still settling, which is the honest home for most ticks agents used to reflexively mark Maximum. Low and VeryLow for leans, proposals, and explicitly-pending-information. Minimum for weak tentative signal. Zero for removal candidates. Certainty is assigned deliberately, never reflexively. *validation*] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (jlo7 ([(Language Rhetoric)] Principle [Guidelines and rules should be worded positively, naming the desired practice to reach for, rather than negatively as a prohibition. Prefer stating what to do over what not to do] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (k09z ([(Safety Privacy)] Constraint [Counselor and assistant act on private personal-affairs material only when the request comes from the owning psyche. Other agents — even ones in privileged lanes — do not authorize cross-lane exposure of private substance by asking;