w loop because the psyche reads Git to see what landed while away. Dirty working copies at pass-end indicate the work isnt finished. Discipline: at the end of every report-shaped or code-shaped pass, commit + push before signing off.] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (ut6z ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [Every registration of a new referent is gated by the guardian, the same as records, not admitted by a self-service synonym check alone *validation*] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (ycmd ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Hand-written Rust is ONLY the engine logic - how to process the objects, the decision-making bodies of actor methods. Everything structural emits from schema: NOTA-encoded form, rkyv binary form, all data type definitions, all enum variants, all field accessors. The engine code does not reinvent the data-structure wheel; it consumes schema-emitted types and writes only logic.] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (zgi8 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [The Spirit guardian is the single locus of judgment and the model checks everything semantic — consistency, duplication, trample, non-intent — with only structural admission staying upstream as input validation] High VeryHigh Zero [])) (0r17 ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Reports are NOT an accumulating archive. Even reports that are still relevant get rewritten/refreshed into current-state reports when context maintenance runs; the older form retires once the new form has carried its substance forward. The goal is a small load-bearing set, not a large historical pile. History lives in jj/git; load-bearing context lives in the current report set.] High High Zero [])) (29pb ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Constraint [Component Sema databases, the daemon durable state, must be backed up to a server atomically, and state loss is unacceptable. Pursue native version-controlled component databases rather than treating the store as an opaque 