nning-concepts-2026-05-26.md - makes the report findable from a chat-only quote, removes the lookup step for the psyche, and matches the path discipline already used inline (skills/intent-clarification.md etc). Per psyche 2026-05-26.|] High High Zero [])) (gad7 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Supersede must support replacing a retired set with multiple new intents in one atomic operation, not just a single replacement. The reason is correctness, not convenience: when the content of the retired records splits into several new records, replacing them with a single record loses meaning and the guardian should refuse it, so superseding with several replacements must be one operation the guardian judges as a whole, asking whether the new set together preserves the kernel of the retired set. *admission control*] High High Zero [])) (ghw7 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|The NOTA brace { } is a STRICT key-value map. Every entry inside braces is exactly TWO objects: a key plus a value, period. The schema language must honor this contract — no single-object entries inside braces. Implications across the stack. Schema namespace body becomes { TypeName TypeDefinition TypeName TypeDefinition ... } where each pair is a new-type declaration: the key is the type name (PascalCase symbol), the value is a positional record like (Newtype Type) / (Struct {...}) / (Enum [...]). Struct body becomes { fieldName TypeRef fieldName TypeRef ... } strictly — explicit field name (camelCase) paired with explicit TypeReference. For the derived-name shorthand (where the field name and the type name would just be the camelCase-of-PascalCase relationship), use a VALUE-SIDE MARKER like (Derive) — a unit-variant marker in the TypeReference enum — instead of single-token entries. So {Topics (Derive) Kind (Derive) Description (Derive)} is the strict form of what was previously {@Topics @Kind @Description}. Bigger architectural generalization: at any brace position the set of valid KEYS is a typed enum (call it KeyEnum). Each key variant determines what type the value carries; sigils on keys distinguish variants (e.g., NewTypeDecl vs Import vs MacroExtension at a namespace position). The schema reader matches the key form (case plus sigil) to the KeyEnum variant, then reads the value as the appropriate type for that variant. This makes the brace a structurally honest key-value map where the KEY is TYPED and the VALUE is DISPATCHED on the key variant — equivalent to a vector of typed enum variants but expressed in brace pair rhythm. The current schema syntax (the @-sigil shorthand inside braces like Entry@{ @Topics @Kind @Description } from records 1232 plus 1235) is DISHONEST about the brace contract because it uses single-token entries inside braces. The syntax needs to be revised — either explicit pairs everywhere or the value-side derive-marker form. Per psyche 2026-05-30.|] High High Zero [])) (hetk ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [|The CLI examples in /312 §5 + §8 (spirit help, spirit help Record, spirit help Slot1 Workspace) violate the single-NOTA-argument rule (AGENTS.md hard override). NO CLI accepts anything except a NOTA string in quotes or a path to a NOTA file. Help retrieval through the CLI is always one NOTA arg: spirit (Help), spirit (Record Help), spirit (Record (Slot1 (Workspace Help)))|] High High Zero [])) (iir4 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl))) (Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [The versioned operation log is the authoritative source of truth for component Sema state, and the redb store becomes a rebuildable materialized view folded from the log. This kernel inversion is chosen for the first version-control implementation rather than deferred.] High High Zero [])) (jh0r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [No stringly-typed types anywhere — the psyche calls them bullshit types. Prefer v