are (Data Serialization)))] Correction [|Signal must be NOTA-free. The signal layer (signal-frame and the signal-component / meta-signal-component contract crates) carries binary/rkyv only and contains no NOTA encoding or projection on its request/reply types. NOTA is a separate text-edge concern that lives outside signal, not a nota-text feature inside the signal crates. This supersedes the nota-text-on-signal projection pattern.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (5jac ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Decision [In a schema, a camelCase or lowercase-first name is a FIELD name, an instance; a PascalCase or capital-first name declares or references a TYPE. A PascalCase type can be declared inline at its first use and then reused by the same name later, which refers back to that inline declaration. Resolution is declare-before-use, left to right: the declaration precedes any reference, so single-pass parsing works without a separate pre-pass. This applies the PascalCase-structural and camelCase-instance rule to the schema field-versus-type distinction and adds inline reusable type declarations.] High Minimum Zero [])) (5trg ([(Information RecordKeeping)] Correction [Spirit record identifiers must not be reused after removal; reuse makes references unstable because a later record can occupy the same identifier.] High Minimum Zero [])) (61ei ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [|Beauty must prevail as a top-priority filter in workspace design and code. Aesthetic quality — terseness symmetry schema-driven self-describing interfaces-first composable-boundaries — is a gate alongside correctness not a nice-to-have. Audits apply the beauty filter as primary lens. Workspace beauty extends beyond code to capture discipline (avoid duplicate intent records) report retention (avoid proliferation without retirement) and substrate cleanliness (no hand-written code where schema can drive).|] High Minimum Zero [])) (6njo ([(Technology (Software (Operat