act event must NOT carry the payloadless SemaObservation classification label. These words belong to sema-engine execution and observation only, never the public contract spine — contract operation roots are domain verbs and the Sema class is something the daemon derives internally, not something a peer sends or names on the wire. This hardens the prior soft guidance that most contracts should-not into a firm prohibition and mandates a cleanup pass now across the six legacy contracts carrying the pattern: signal-mind, signal-router, and signal-criome with its AuthorizedSignalVerb enum, plus owner-signal-persona, signal-persona-spirit, and signal-orchestrate whose EffectEmitted SemaObservation event gets a non-Sema label. Distinct from and milder than the engine-trait and plane leak of record 2593, but forbidden on the same wire-only principle.] High Minimum Zero [])) (7m2d ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Correction [Lojix deployment is not the problem to avoid; the safety issue is local resource pressure during build/evaluation, so operator work should keep using lojix while making the workload safe.] High Minimum Zero [])) (7mvx ([(Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Principle [Relevance, duplication, and contradiction between intent records are semantic judgments that only a model can make, so the guardian evidence bundle sent to the judge is never filtered or capped by a deterministic relevance score; instead the relevance call is made by a model once at write time and stored as a referent for cheap scoped reuse, and the input is bounded by referent or domain scoping and by corpus agglomeration, never by heuristic truncation of the model evidence] High Minimum Zero [])) (7nbu ([(Work Vocation)] Principle [Designer's deliverable is intent / architecture / skills, not reports] High Minimum Zero [])) (853n ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Spirit record identifiers should be stable, non-reusable handles. Removin