ace impl block with the target implicit, so a type and its trait participations and method signatures are introduced together at the declaration and there are no separate marker objects to associate with their type by hand, because separate objects add too much association complexity. Inside the impl block each entry is a bare trait atom for a marker impl, or a trait atom followed by a bracket of method signatures for a body-bearing trait impl, or a bare method signature for an inherent method; a method signature is the method name then a brace parameter struct then a return type, the same shape as a Work-frame leg, listing a callable signature of a referenced existing impl rather than a generated body. Method calls resolve from the receiver schema shape plus this fused impl catalog. Generating method bodies from schema stays reserved for the narrow mechanical family; deref-by-default is not a goal, it was only scaffolding for impl syntax.] High Minimum Zero [nota nota-next schema-next schema-cc])) (bc6f ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [CriomOS FullOS deploys must carry the latest CriomOS-home fixes by updating the production CriomOS flake lock before deploying Zeus.] High Minimum Zero [])) (bev5 ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [Home profile activation must persist across reboot; a reboot that restores an older deployed Claude version is a system bug to investigate rather than acceptable behavior.] High Minimum Zero [])) (bexd ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [Component feedback, status, and error reporting is expressed as typed self-descriptive NOTA enums and structs whose names carry the meaning, not as long string description messages. A result type should be so well named it needs no accompanying message string — our own feedback language built from enums and structs decoded through NOTA. This specializes strings-only-at-the-edges to the messaging surface and should be manifeste