ion [Every code or logic change to a component must bump the component version, at minimum the patch component such as 0.3.0 to 0.3.1, so changes stay trackable across the fast-moving stack. Versions had been lagging — 0.3 dates to roughly last week despite many changes since. A versioning skill should carry this discipline — an agent who changes logic bumps the version as part of the same change.] High Minimum Zero [])) (hh3z ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems))) (Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Decision [|A type's kind is announced by the delimiter that wraps its value, the same way a brace body means struct and a square-bracket body means enum. Generics use the reserved pipe-parenthesis delimiter (| ... |), pipes inside, mirroring the existing pipe-text string delimiter. A generic declaration is Name (| [params] body |): the pipe-parenthesis marks the type generic, the params are the binder list, and the body is an ordinary struct or enum body nested inside. This assigns meaning to one of the two reserved pipe-bracket extension points named by j9du; nota-next already parses these blocks (PipeParenthesis and PipeBrace delimiters exist), so it is schema-level work, not a seed-parser change. Realizes j9du and satisfies 3742.|] High Minimum Zero [nota nota-next schema-next])) (hu8i ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [Schema and schema-emitted Rust should sit on top of the same NOTA typed interfaces that direct Rust code uses. Reusing NOTA decode encode traits is better engineering than emitting a parallel mini-codec for each generated schema.] High Minimum Zero [])) (hv5f ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [When the existing shape does not fit, follow where the logic wants to go rather than being bound by what is already there — let the water find where it wants to go downhill. Desire paths name this: the trail walked into the grass because that is how the body naturally moves, regardles