 root field names input output namespace live once in the known root type, never repeated per file - the root already has names. Consequence: the current four-position document that writes labeled Input and Output positions does not match this; honoring it drops those labels, even in root.schema. Single requirement: the root kind must be known from OUTSIDE the bytes - extension or load context - like a Nix derivation whose shape you know before filling it.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (l8ox ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [|Internal representation uses FULLY QUALIFIED NAMES: crate::module::type form. The AssembledSchema prefixes the module name in front of every type. Good for debugging (you know exactly what crate + what schema). When the macro outputs modules per schema, the qualification becomes natural. Single thing per name per context invariant - if an import clashes with a local name in the same context that should error not silently shadow.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (lmzl ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Principle [|Workspace preferred data extension shape is enum or vector-of-enum-variants. Vector IS structurally an enum — gives choice of all things that can be in it. Maps are reserved for namespaces specifically. Bool with True/False PascalCase is conceptually a two-unit-variant enum — this is why NOTA capitalizes them. Variants are unit (bare PascalCase) or data-carrying (parenthesized), in order, positional.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (lrfa ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Value lean, efficient design and do not fear breaking things. Breakage belongs in development, not production; breaking freely in development is what development is for. Lean means no duplication and no boilerplate, not the fewest lines.] High Minimum Zero [])) (lyo2 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Decision [|NOTA is a thin library for sense-of-structure - it exposes methods on parsed blocks (is_square_bracket / is_parenthesis / is_brace / holds_N_objects / qualifies_as_symbol / etc) that are macro primitives. People use NOTA to design any positional uncompromisingly-specific domain-specific configuration data language. NOTA itself does not interpret meaning; it delivers structure to the upper layer (macros / schema) which interpret.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (mlq0 ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Constraint [Spirit operations should report outcomes with self-describing NOTA enums and structs instead of long free-text status messages wherever the state can be represented as typed data. *error handling*] High Minimum Zero [])) (mn66 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Spirit record certainty is optional at the persona-spirit entry boundary rather than a None variant inside shared Magnitude vocabulary; the absence semantics stay local to Spirit records.] High Minimum Zero [])) (mq6u ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [Parenthesized variants carry data.] High Minimum Zero [])) (mqlb ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Decision [|Move the schema declaration out of Rust macros into a specialized NOTA-format schema language. The current signal_channel! macro AND the planned sema-side macro converge with the earlier-started NOTA schema language work (designer/263 + /279). The NOTA schema is the SOURCE; the codegen produces (a) Rust types and impls (the macro current role), (b) per-version namespace-slot-assignment tables, (c) version-diff that auto-marks types for upgrade-migration when the schema is recompiled across versions. The macro becomes a consumer of structured schema data, not a parser of Rust syntax. The NOTA schema is human-readable enough to keep portions of it editable; compilation handles slot-number assignment + size optimization automatically.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (mrcx ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Principle [|NOTA is made to be embedded inline everywhere host strings appear (Rust source, JSON, Nix attribute values, env vars, shell arguments). The embedded NOTAs meaning is derived from where it is, based on the schema applicable at that embedding site. The bracket-only string discipline that makes NOTA embedding-safe in double-quote host strings is the carrier mechanism; schema is the interpretation mechanism at each site.|] High Minimum Zero [])) (mrkv ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [Spirit capture is a blocking gate not an advisory check: the guardian must vet and admit a proposed record before capture succeeds, so duplicates, contradictions, compounds, and non-intent are resolved or refused at the door rather than admitted and cleaned up later *validation*] High Minimum Zero [])) (mtrx ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [Spirit should support removal-candidate review as a first-class observation flow, using record certainty or magnitude so low-confidence records can be found before removal rather than hard-deleted ad hoc.] High Minimum Zero [])) (mx58 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Decision [The schema language is a reusable macro-lowered structured declaration bedrock, not only a Spirit contract format.] High Minimum Zero [])) (my4g ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [|Persona uses systemd for component daemon management in production via template units (persona-component@<component>:<version>.service) from day one; UnitController trait with systemd-D-Bus backend (prod) + direct-fork backend (tests/sandbox) *orchestration*|] High Minimum Zero [])) (n5ch ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [|NOTA mirrors the binary self-describing root object plus relative-pointer box layout. For complex schemas, the root object stays compact (sized fields inline); unsized or growing fields (String, Vec, Option-of-unsized, nested records with their own growth) become BOXES that appear AFTER the root in decla