entation; when the psyche asks an agent to implement work, the agent should work the bead or code path immediately unless blocked.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0b9q ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [NOTA pipe text should use a normal escape character for literal close-marker text instead of widening pipe fences indefinitely. The string codec should keep one readable pipe-text delimiter shape and escape payload content that would otherwise close it.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0be2 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Schema files create the data types for the libraries they serve and may live side by side with Rust source when that is the simplest working layout; the schema remains the source of data-type truth.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0dys ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [Spirit operations should support a simpler-to-more-complex variant ladder — short forms with summary defaults for normal/common operations, complex forms with full metadata for custom/precise operations. The ladder lets the psyche or agent choose the right explicitness level per moment. Short forms serve daily use without the cognitive cost of full NOTA; complex forms preserve precise control for cases that need it. Both shapes coexist in the wire vocabulary as distinct operation roots; the complex root is canonical, the short root expands to a default form of the complex root.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0fdy ([(Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [Component databases use a .sema file extension instead of .redb, hiding redb behind our own .sema file type so the file name states it is specifically a sema-redb database. Reinforces the direction that the storage file name declares its architectural role rather than exposing the raw redb engine. *storage*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0fmg ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [|The Spirit CLI must be documented thoroughly enough that agents do not have to scramble on first contact. Documentation covers: invocation (inline NOTA argument vs file-path argument), every operation (Record, State, Observe, Watch, Unwatch), the deployed wire shape and how to find it when source drifts from production, error replies, environment variables, and observability. The skills/spirit-cli.md file is the canonical home; intent-log.md points there.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0ofm ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint [Schema work must be tested end-to-end with actual .schema files and local relative imports *integration testing*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0q0u ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Schema files can be split by contract or schema-file type so parsing is per file and positional over root NOTA objects rather than one overloaded monolithic file.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0qda ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Principle [Gap-fill from forwarded designer prompt: the schema macro system is the basis for domain-specific interaction languages across components and actors, turning delimiter-shaped NOTA into typed input-output interfaces.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (0srq ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|Schema file is a STRUCT at root - implied by the .schema extension; no explicit root declaration needed. First field of the schema struct is the imports/exports namespace (curly-bracket map). Subsequent positional field(s) are input/output struct(s) in square brackets. When both input and output are present they may live as a single combined struct field (since-both-are-present framing); single-sided schemas have only the present side. Optionality applies to which sub-fields appear inside the struct, not to having separate sections.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1352 ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [Version migration is per type] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (15n7 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Psyche-facing audits and presentations should show the primordial typed text forms at the layers where text is the representation, including NOTA and schema source, so the line of thought is visible through concrete code rather than only abstract prose.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (17l9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [|Extension of Spirit 1467 inline enum-payload pattern. The inline enum-body list can declare variant NAMES without distinguishing unit vs data-carrying in the header. When a variant name in the inline list is defined elsewhere as a newtype/struct/named type the variant is data-carrying with that type as its payload; when not defined elsewhere it is a unit variant. The header doesn't need to know which — the codec resolves against the type table. Lets the inline enum-body form fit data-carrying variants while staying compact. Example — Output [RecordAccepted Rejected Busy MaintenanceMode] works even if RecordAccepted and Rejected are defined elsewhere as data-carrying newtypes (wrapping SemaReceipt and SignalRejection respectively) and Busy/MaintenanceMode are unit. Sugar feature; cleaner schemas; less paren noise at variant-list positions.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (17ss ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Principle [Router-acknowledgement = delivery durable on harness-side ack *message queuing*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (18cb ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces Visualization)))] Constraint [|Visuals in reports MUST be mermaid diagrams; no ASCII text-block diagrams (they are error-prone and not real diagrams). Encode in skills/reporting.md|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1924 ([(Technology (Software (Operations ConfigurationManagement)))] Decision [If VSCodium is enabled in a CriomOS-home profile, it should be the default editor for file-opening links and editor MIME handling for now, including Markdown and source files such as Rust.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1g6p ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Durable Spirit identity should not rely on reusable incremental numbers; unique hashes are a better identity direction, while recency tracking should use daemon-stamped time.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1i1b ([(Language Terminology)] Clarification [|When the psyche says 'signal' (the noun, on its own), the term is ambiguous: it may refer to the rkyv-encoded binary signal traveling on a socket or to the NOTA-encoded text signal that agents read and write. Disambiguation is required when context does not pin the form. Psyche proposed the term 'nota signal' for the text form (softly: 'I guess we could call it'); the term is therefore proposed but not yet hardened into workspace vocabulary.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1i53 ([(Work Leadership)] Decision [|Automate the auditor; DeepSeek is the main auditor going forward (audits are mechanical, suit a smaller model good at rules-and-flaws detection)|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1kfk ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [|Chat replies must include the report PATH (not just commit hash or report number) as the locator whenever a report is referenced. Per psyche 2026-05-30 after a chat reply that gave the commit hash and report number but omitted the path. The path is what lets the user open the report directly without translating mentally. Format: reports/designer/NNN-slug.md or similar. Applies to: chat replies that reference a report just created, chat replies that reference an existing report, audit replies that compare reports, follow-up replies. Generalizes the locator-substance rule in skills/reporting.md (chat-vs-report discipline). The path IS the locator's substantive part.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1ozj ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|Persona Pi is a real persona-component triad — the Pi harness adapted for the persona system. Lives as its own component-tree (daemon + signal-persona-pi working contract + owner-signal-persona-pi policy contract + thin pi CLI client). Runs inside a terminal-cell (the persona-terminal-shaped surface that handles Unix-side I/O), but is NOT confined to it: Persona Pi can also talk directly to the harness API. The terminal-cell is the Unix-interaction conduit; the harness-API path is the more accessible logic surface, used because Pi is extensively customizable and exposes far more than terminal I/O.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1q5w ([(Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [|The recording system's intent-capture stage (currently sketched in /145 §6) is a per-call runtime LLM function, not an agent. It receives speech-to-text output, extracts intent for logging, may rephrase to clean STT typos / structure thoughts better, and may route sections of the prompt to different long-lived agents based on topic. The function has no persistent identity; it's invoked per audio span. Long-lived agents (the ones with cryptographic identity per intent 120) consume the routed prompt sections; the intent-capture itself stays stateless. This refines /145's design — the extractor was described neutrally as 'the model'; the function-vs-agent distinction makes the call's shape explicit and unlocks the per-call context provisioning pattern.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1rci ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Clarification [NOTA braces are the native structural key-value map delimiter. Schema reads a brace object as key-value structure, not as a schema macro form. Key-value-ness belongs to the low-level NOTA structure; macros may consume these structures at schema positions.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (1sa2 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Correction [Schema/module-system correction: braces are structurally key-value maps; namespace is conceptually dynamic-enum-like; fully qualified schema names should use a single-colon namespace separator; crates carry schema/lib.schema entrypoints and schema modules; generated Rust emits into a schema mod