ntrol)))] Constraint [Lock selectively: claim only the specific files or subfolders you will edit, never the whole workspace. Reports are claim-exempt — report lanes are per-role and need no lock per record 1566 — and agents keep forgetting this, so it must be reinforced in several places. Over-locking the whole workspace is a root cause of the branch-dancing on primary; lock narrowly and just work on main.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2cuo ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Principle [|Everything in the schema reduces to STRUCTS (data-carrying) or UNIT VARIANTS. Vec is a struct with a single field. Enum data-carrying variants ARE structs - the data-carrying portion IS the struct shape. Macros are structs. Even unit variants live inside enum structs in some sense. The reduction simplifies the type system: one canonical kind (struct) plus the unit case. Field naming + composition all derive from this.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2dzp ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [The key-value-map collection type is named KeyValue - not KeyValueMap and not Map. Map alone risks being read as a verb, and the Map suffix is redundant once key and value are named. So the collection macros are Vec, Option, and KeyValue, each a parenthesised form with the keyword as head: KeyValue followed by key type then value type. Refines record 1034 which had proposed KeyValueMap.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2f04 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Clarification [|Formalizes Spirit 1395 — an interface is an enum at the root with MORE THAN ONE variant. If a designer cannot name more than one operation the root represents the design is incomplete and not an interface. Single-variant enums prove themselves newtypes in practice. Input and Output are the two primary interface roots; payloads are themselves either structs (leaf data) or enums (nested interfaces). The interface chain depth measures design realism.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2gj4 ([(Work Vocation)] Decision [|Add a third role — the auditor — that closes the loop back to designer; audits are mostly mechanical (doubter, finds flaws / bad patterns / broken workspace rules); auditor knows the rules|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2hi3 ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Decision [Build configuration is itself a NOTA struct with fields — the same single-NOTA-argument rule that governs daemon and CLI input also governs build configuration. Testing-build is a configurable field on that struct; how the build switches between production and testing modes is the same NOTA-shaped declaration as the rest of the build config.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2qhw ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [|lojix-daemon takes scope expansion to handle GitHub-authenticated Nix flake input resolution. The GitHub API rate-limit stale-activation incident (per reports/cluster-operator/7 file:54-64) is a deploy-path problem owned by lojix, not a Pi-package problem. Resolves Open Question 7.2 from reports/system-designer/31 in favor of lojix-daemon scope expansion over skill-level discipline. Mechanism: an authenticated wrapper around the relevant Nix invocation that fetches the user GitHub API key from gopass and injects it into the Nix call (likely via NIX_CONFIG access-tokens). Implementation form (Medium certainty per the parenthetical): a small Rust library that lojix-daemon calls; the library encapsulates the secret-fetch + auth-injection so the rest of lojix-daemon does not handle the token directly. *provisioning*|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2qia ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Principle [Root signal shapes should generally begin with an enum that differentiates input and output spaces. Explicit variant numbering over an 8-bit root enum can reserve numeric ranges for those spaces while keeping dispatch cheap.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (2szc ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [