tion)))] Decision [Sema upgrade should become a component for updating Sema databases] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (69jq ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Constraint [Import/name clashes fail within a schema context] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (6cm6 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Constraint [Schema language macros must expand into a fully one-to-one assembled tree that describes all generated types, API endpoint variant names, and the input structs carried by those variants before Rust code is emitted.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (6i29 ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [operators read peer operator reports first] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (6jdv ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Principle [Schema files contribute a namespace prefix, initially their file name, so locally-defined names can be resolved and imported through schema namespaces without collapsing into one global flat name space.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (6ks1 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|Cloud compute nodes use a billing-hour-aware reuse pool: an idle recently-created node still within its already-paid billing window is reused for a matching request instead of delete-and-recreate, and idle nodes are reaped before they cross into a new paid billing period. The keep-warm duration (how long a node is kept warm and reusable by default after it spins down) is a per-provider setting derived from the provider billing granularity; for Hetzner (hourly billing) it is 59 minutes, anchored to the billing-hour boundary so the full paid hour stays reusable and the reaper fires before a second hour starts. The larger benefit is latency from skipping create, boot and install, not only the reclaimed paid-hour cost.|] Medium Minimum Zero [cloud])) (6oun ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Principle [|The three NOTA delimiters correspond to the three schema sections. Parentheses are for enum/variant header forms (the schema's user