sed before T. More broadly, every quorum-signed object carries an attested moment - a quorum signature is never timeless but is always over content together with a crystallized moment - so every admission envelope, oracle verdict, agreement fact, and operation is time-bound for freshness and replay reasoning. The AttestedMoment itself is the self-grounding base case: it carries no inner moment, because its own window and quorum signatures are the time proof, which stops the regress.] Medium Minimum Zero [criome])) (b0v3 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Decision [Schema files use dot-schema extension] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (b1c4 ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Clarification [Upgrade and downgrade are one compatibility projection relation] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (b9ao ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Principle [The persona system is federated at its core. Each persona triad - mind + orchestrator + spirit plus future components - is one federated unit. Eventually orchestrators across personas and across namespaces become aware of each other s subtasks they have sent as communication. They interface via skilled-agent subtasks; each persona offers itself as a thing-with-context whose opinion can be queried. The persona abstraction creates the another-AI-meta-system-over-there substrate that makes federation natural rather than special-cased. *distributed systems*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (ba22 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [Schema top-level vectors are typed schema objects, not one flat mixed vector.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bb83 ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Clarification [Cross-daemon cutover can be atomic by protocol *fault tolerance*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bds6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Keep the active repository set lean. Superseded, dead, duplicate, and stub repositories are archived rather than left to clutter the workspace; a smaller active set is better. 150 active repos is too many. *maintenance*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (beue ([(Work Vocation)] Clarification [Concept designer is an ephemeral occasional invocation, not a persistent named lane] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bhs5 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Principle [|The `[| \|]` block string form is useful as a safe wrapper for multiline NOTA-like content that does not contain the block delimiter itself.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (biij ([(Technology (Software Quality))] Constraint [Rename only after confirming there are no external source dependents. *refactoring*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bnxx ([(Language Terminology)] Correction [|The engine-manager daemon's canonical short name is 'Persona' (just Persona) — not 'Persona Engine Manager Daemon' and not 'engine-manager daemon'. The longer 'Persona engine' (used in intent records 208/209) is acceptable but the simpler 'Persona' is preferred. Concrete name surfaces: repo is 'persona' (lowercase, /git/github.com/LiGoldragon/persona); daemon binary is 'persona-daemon'; conceptual entity is 'Persona'. Engine-manager is the ROLE (what the daemon does); 'Persona' is the NAME. When agents reference this in reports, beads, intent records, or chat, default to 'Persona' for the entity and 'engine-management' for the role/relation.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bpg9 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [A .asschema file is read against the known Asschema root struct, so the canonical text form should not need an outer parenthesized record wrapper. The reader can consume the root fields positionally from the document root objects, using delimiters to find each field boundary.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (bpry ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [Schema upgrade knowledge belongs to the next version, which assembles against the previous schema.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (brgo ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture))