erface. During a live upgrade transition, the old database and the migrated new database both run; the SEMA interface owns this concurrency.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (qxye ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Constraint [Bird/Aether has her own forked workspace and soul repositories] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (qy15 ([(Safety Privacy)] Decision [Private intent capture gains an explicit named short-form operation such as RecordPrivate or RecordSealed so capturing private material is one deliberate hard-to-forget ritual rather than remembering to set a privacy field. The default record visibility stays public at privacy Zero; private capture is opt-in but unmissable through the named form.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit])) (qyny ([(Technology (Software Data))] Principle [Internal database logic should use the same schema-defined message language as component signals: the daemon may keep the database engine internal for now, but a growing database component can split into its own daemon without changing the language pattern. *database systems*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (qz6j ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Decision [In schema-next the bare form of a name followed by a type declares a distinct newtype, not a non-distinct alias; this is the safe common intent of the typed-values discipline. Aliases lose the bare form, so they are dropped or kept only as an explicit rarely-used marked form. The single-field struct form is no longer the only way to declare a newtype] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (r08u ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Clarification [Schema names must resolve from defined namespaces or imports, with Spirit allowed to define all types locally for the MVP.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (r0a2 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|The 'interact trait' formulation from records 660 + 665 + 666 was the wrong shape for the right intuition. The actual intent: SCHEMAS WARRANT FROM