 = struct with positional fields; (fieldname [variants]) = inline enum field with explicit name. The executor assembles the full schema by resolving paths and references.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wipc ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [Schema headers are enum namespace nodes, not one payload pair per verb.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wiq2 ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [The basic schema-emitted type definitions should derive NOTA traits and rkyv traits from the same data objects. Additional communication traits belong on the generated schema root objects when those objects cross component boundaries.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wqdi ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Principle [Multi-argument type references and applications use NOTA's flat positional form — head then arguments inline, like Map then K then V — not a grouped form that wraps the arguments in their own delimiters. The head already names the construct, so a trained human or LLM reads the positional arguments correctly without extra grouping, and the flat form is fewer characters while staying equally legible. This settles the Map type-reference shape as the flat head-K-V form and generalizes to multi-argument type-reference applications.] Medium Minimum Zero [nota-next schema-next])) (wr8s ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Decision [Crate name for the VersionProjection home is version-projection, peer to signal-sema] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wrjl ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [|Design direction (refining intent record 12 schema-in-NOTA): each persona contract carries an explicit schema-layout schema written in a NOTA-based language. The schema-layout description is fully content-addressable — its hash is its identity. Any edit to the schema changes the address, which is the version. The version-checking pipeline (built into component handling) detects schema-address mismatches between current code and stored data, walks the diff between addresses, and derives the migration operations (zero-cost variant extensions, append-only struct fields, structural migrations) from the diff. The migratory process is baked into how the types are written rather than written separately. More sophisticated than Cap'n Proto. Warrants deep testing and investigation before committing to a concrete shape.|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wsgh ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Clarification [MigrationIndex is a runtime decoder lookup] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wtaz ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Vector sugar is structurally a single-field container object] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wv7w ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [Schema diffs should be isolated as typed upgrade operations.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wvrt ([(Work Productivity)] Decision [After active implementation/prototype subagent work, run context maintenance and a fresh-intent audit over recent reports and code before deciding what to address immediately. The main operator should synthesize the returned work, choose sensible immediate fixes, and implement them rather than letting stale context drive the next slice.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wxip ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Help and documentation should be schema data in a mirror description namespace over the global symbol namespace, with generated defaults when no explicit description entry exists for a fully qualified symbol.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (wywp ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [For large schema implementation and synthesis tasks, the operator should use subagents in parallel when explicitly authorized, with the main agent staying responsible for integration, constraints, tests, and the final report.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (x020 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [A single string that qualifies as a symbol name must be encoded in NOTA as a bare symbol, not quoted with brackets. Bracket strings are not the representation for schema names that are symbol-safe.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (x2su ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [input and output are PARTITIONS of a single enum tag space - not two separate independent enums but two halves of one tag namespace at the wire level; the conceptual split for a 1-byte enum carrying ~240 slots is approximately two-thirds: first ~120 slots reserved for INPUT variants, slots ~121 to ~240 reserved for OUTPUT variants; this means at the wire byte level a single tag byte identifies BOTH the variant and whether the message is an input or output by which range it falls in; the schema author declares Input and Output separately at the schema level but the rkyv-compiled binary form merges them into one tag space; this is also the conceptual basis for the structural header at the message layer - first byte tells you immediately whether to dispatch on input handlers or output handlers; the specific 240-slot 120-120 split is illustrative not locked - larger enums get larger spaces *encoding*] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (x2yz ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Clarification [|Per-repo data-type discipline (signal-X repos with versioned schema libraries) is what enables cross-version decoding and recovery|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (x3m9 ([(Technology (Software (Operations DependencyManagement)))] Principle [Development Nix inputs may point at feature branch names for mutable role lanes] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (x4tx ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Three-tier signal type sizing: (1) 64-bit micro-message — the default auto-loggable variant every Signal Operation/Reply/Effect/SemaObservation implements via macro, packing root variant tag plus packed sub-discriminators into a u64; (2) 64-byte summary message — hand-implemented when a type has natural summary fields (public key + metadata, short string, etc.) —