iomOS should gain a node feature for VM-based testing using the best available Linux virtual-machine technology, to properly test CriomOS itself and its components — including visual/UI/GPU cases such as chroma's gamma warmth and brightness that a headless sandbox cannot exercise (report 66 found headless wlroots has no wlr-gamma-control). The feature provides a real display/GPU/DRM-capable VM, ideally Nix-native and automatable for CI as well as interactively viewable. *e2e*|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (y3tc ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Generated modules may mirror schema-file contexts to avoid name clashes] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (y88n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [The contract-daemon and engine-stack split should have Spirit as a proper exemplar; Spirit must not be left as an all-in-one pilot that agents describe as an explicitly non-copyable shape.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (y94z ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Decision [The workspace skills must state the secret-handling discipline explicitly: gopass wrapping of environment variables, sops-nix cluster secret storage, and the never-show-a-secret rule, so every agent applies it the same way.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (ydpa ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Principle [Macro loading uses a FIRST INDEXING PASS that collects all macro names declared in the schema and its imports BEFORE any macro is invoked. Subsequent passes resolve macro references by name from the index. This enables forward references and out-of-order definitions because macros can reference macros declared later or in imported modules. Lazy loading: a macro is loaded only when referenced by name during dispatch.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (yenl ([(Information Curation)] Clarification [|Clarification of the one-capturer-per-multi-lane-prompt rule: the default capturer is the lane that RESPONDS FIRST, not the designer. In practice that is