g the asschema roundtrip design, prefer simple canonical NOTA syntax and separated typed-object responsibilities: Asschema owns assembled schema data, AsschemaArtifact owns NOTA and rkyv artifact projection, a SEMA store owns durable rkyv persistence, and Rust emission consumes the typed Asschema object rather than parsing side syntax.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (yvez ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Decision [The schema Rust emission should split Signal Nexus and SEMA into separate emitted namespaces now, so plane payloads can use simple names like Input and Output inside their plane namespace instead of carrying redundant plane prefixes.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (yy76 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [Create a standard engine situation report discipline that summarizes components, production code size, schema size, generated Rust size, interfaces, signatures, and graphs so agents and the psyche can quickly understand a system.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (yzwg ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Universal data variants pre-allocated across all signal namespaces (U8, U16, possibly more primitive types). Every namespace inherits these as primitive sub-variants. Use cases: Criome 16-bit short ID for its public key (so all logs carry the short ID for human readability); generic counters; small fixed-size values shared across components|] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (z1yz ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Constraint [Schema must have a schema-authored self-description even while the bootstrap Rust reader remains hand-written. The schema file that defines how to read schema files is required as a tested artifact: it does not have to be load-bearing for the reader yet, but it must lower through the current engine and expose the root Schema shape and nested declaration types clearly.] Medium Minimum Zero [])) (z2nx ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Principl