ient can connect to. Each remains an ordinary component with its two contracts; the split is about deployment instances and privilege tiers, not extra contracts. For now the single owner - the psyche - holds the system root privilege through the home criome. The Mentci approval daemon also running its own criome is an instance of the same per-principal-criome pattern. Exploratory and for-development - the psyche is not sure yet.] Low Minimum Zero [criome])) (9s52 ([(Technology (Software (Security Authorization))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Constraint [criome is per-Unix-user: each user runs their own home criome daemon with their own key custody, and the operating-system Unix-user boundary is the trust boundary. There is no single shared system criome that multiple users connect to with in-process separated lanes - that would collapse every user behind one daemon and one compromise point, a security risk. The privileged system criome tier from 9qm8 is for host-scoped system services under a service user, not a multi-user shared daemon; a user home criome peers with it for host-level facts rather than users sharing one criome. This is the same single-Unix-user custody boundary that rules out an embeddable criome engine library.] Low Minimum Zero [criome])) (amab ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Clarification [The input-output split can be represented in the root enum namespace by reserving variant number ranges, so one first-byte header can distinguish request-like input variants from response-like output variants for the same actor mechanism.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (arb2 ([(Work Productivity)] Decision [|Long-term direction for intent recording: spirit-CLI-driven, intent-recording-of-role for all roles, in real-time, with Prometheus running the continuous capture. The chat-mediated capture pattern (psyche prompt → agent extracts intent → spirit-CLI record) gives way over time to direct real-time recording across every 