erdict criome only verifies. That verdict is a closed typed outcome over an already-submitted content-addressed object, not a carrier for newly-authored answer content. Criome only authorizes objects that come in for authorization. Program answers live inside the program's declared closed answer set. The Mentci/criome adjudication path is vote-on-existing-object: approve the suggested object, reject it, or defer/non-judge/escalate. If Mentci lets the psyche author a NOTA value - for example an LLM prompt, a replacement answer proposal, or another typed object - that is a separate editor and object-creation flow; the authored value must be admitted as its own content-addressed object before criome can authorize it. Two properties make the ladder humble and adaptive. First, non-judgment is a first-class adjudicator output: an adjudicator may decline to rule and escalate instead of forcing a verdict. Second, the default LLM adjudicator is trained to lean toward rendering non-judgment - abstaining and escalating to a smarter agent or agents and to a psyche or psyches - rather than deciding a case it is not confident in or that is too contentious. So the cheap default judge resolves the clear cases and bows out of the hard ones, spending scarce smart-agent and human attention only where it is genuinely needed; the psyche is the highest-authority and lowest-availability adjudicator. This is the architectural expression of intent-is-primordial: when a contract or a judge cannot or should not decide, it defers upward, ultimately to the human. Reaching the psyche adjudicator depends on a psyche-facing UI: until that UI exists the EscalateToPsyche outcome is intentionally an inert dead-letter and not a defect, because the terminal human rung is gated on the interface that lets a psyche receive and answer escalations.] Low Minimum Zero [criome])) (iprx ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Decision [Cloud credential custody is moving toward system-level credentials: the current model, a wire-supplied CredentialHandle the cloud daemon resolves to a process environment variable behind the 0o600 owner socket, is accepted as the transitional shape, and the eventual direction is system-custodied machine credentials following the criome-custodied machine-identity pattern of h03z rather than a wire-selected environment variable name.] Low Minimum Zero [cloud meta-signal-cloud CredentialHandle])) (iq57 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Nexus may be modeled as a recursive computation destination: when more work needs to happen, the next object is a Nexus object rather than a final reply. Nexus can carry objects originating from Signal, SEMA, or other effect/computation schemas, because schemas can contain and import objects from other schema parts. The design should explore Nexus as the universal computation continuation while preserving clear directional meanings for requests, commands, replies, and final Signal output.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (j60y ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [parallel subagents receive report lanes before launch] Low Minimum Zero [])) (j9du ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [NOTA's own grammar can be schema-described, making the notation self-hosting. Its delimiter set is a closed enum: the three base pairs parenthesis, square-bracket, brace, plus three piped variants pipe-parenthesis, pipe-text, and pipe-brace. The pipe-text delimiter is already defined and used by NOTA for bracket-safe and multiline strings. The pipe-parenthesis and pipe-brace delimiters exist in the grammar but carry no assigned meaning, and are reserved as extension points for extended NOTA languages such as schema to define their own constructs. Schema-ing NOTA closes the self-describing loop: schema describes the contracts, the structural macro nodes, and NOTA itself.] Low Minimum Zero [nota-next])) (jqvu ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [Generic enum field syntax should use parentheses, not vector brackets.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (jvpe ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Principle [Cloud provider support should be build-selectable; unsupported provider requests return a typed unsupported-capability reply, with future self-upgrade possible when support is cheaply available.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (l3ca ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|Each agent role gets its own workspace — a sub-workspace that is its own Git repository (called role-space, even though psyche acknowledges the name is awkward). Write access is gated via Git push, which is gated on the agent's SSH key (set when the agent starts). Each role has its own research lane within this space. This is the substrate that backs per-role isolation: designer-space, operator-space, poet-space, etc., each a separate repository whose push permissions are bound to whichever agent is currently in that role. (Designing-mode speculation — much of this is not yet implemented; intent recorded so the design direction is captured.)|] Low Minimum Zero [])) (lc28 ([(Technology (Software (Operations ConfigurationManagement)))] Decision [For the lojix cutover, substituter resolution from node name to Yggdrasil cache URL and public key moves into the daemon: the daemon gains horizon-read for substituters and the wire reverts to carrying bare node names instead of pre-resolved url and public-key pairs. This is a for-now choice and the implementing code must be explicitly marked as must be replaced by better design, not treated as the final shape. Resolves the substituter-resolution-location question in favour of option a, provisionally.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (lvy9 ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [|Real-time streaming support is a new signal capability (working name signal-real-time) *stream processing*|] Low Minimum Zero [])) (mz3p ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [active report lanes should stay well below twelve] Low Minimum Zero []))