ng to that spec, instead of hand-coded as a Rust shape derive. Then the layer that decodes NOTA would itself be defined in NOTA. This points to building that schema specification for the structural macro node.] Low Minimum Zero [nota-next schema-next])) (td4h ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Clarification [|The schema type library (the macro substrate) MAY live in a separate repo from the schema component daemon if separation works better organizationally. Two possible shapes: (i) co-located — schema component triad holds daemon + the schema-types library in the same repo; (ii) separated — a dedicated schema-types library repo distinct from the schema component triad, both consuming the same compiled NOTA schema artifacts. Lean unsettled; depends on whether the library carries a meaningfully different release cadence from the daemon, and whether other consumers of the library would prefer to depend on a small library crate rather than pulling in the triad scaffolding. The compiled schema artifact (binary form per spirit 398) is the same in both shapes; only the crate-layout differs.|] Low Minimum Zero [])) (u2s9 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Spirit entry weight is intended as a set record axis, not only a computed search score: agglomerating several related intents into one record should preserve their accumulated importance through a higher weight, because after compaction the source mentions are no longer visible as separate active records. This weight-field design is low-certainty and should be revisited before production implementation.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (uuu9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Principle [Assembled schema should make names globally unambiguous by context] Low Minimum Zero [])) (uxiz ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Clarification [Single-object sigil sugar is an open macro-node design frontier: a leading sigil can eventually make one NOTA object stand