ignal in, nexus through, sema state, output back). Plain schema says what data IS; reactive schema says how data MOVES. Most schemas are plain; a component top-level schema is reactive. Naming proposed by the psyche; pending the schema-syntax design conversation settling.|] Low Minimum Zero [])) (ychx ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Decision [|Bracket semantics swap: () is for enum/variants and [] is for struct/fields. Structural justification: a struct IS a vector of fields (all present positionally - matches [] vector semantics); an enum IS one-of from alternatives (matches () grouping/variant semantics). This REVERSES /326-v13s convention where [...] was sequence/enum and (...) was record/struct. Touches every existing .schema file + operator/181+/182+/190 implementations + intent 614 field-naming form. Reading: Entry [Topic Kind Summary] is a struct (6 fields); Kind (Decision Principle Correction) is an enum (one-of). Container expressions: (Vec T) stays () since Vec is a single-tagged-variant form; or [Vec T] under stricter reading - needs clarification.|] Low Minimum Zero [])) (z5aw ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Principle [Future forge build logic may let generated Rust code become content-addressed crates directly, reducing the need for separate generated-code repositories once forge can own that build path outside Nix.] Low Minimum Zero [])) (z9kv ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Clarification [Proposed: the schema TYPE - which of the three planes a schema declares - is a Kind enum, schema::Kind, with Sema Nexus and Signal DATA variants, each variant carrying that planes schema body. So a schema documents root is a Kind value such as Sema wrapping that planes 4-position content. This resolves record 964s open question of how the schema type is declared in favour of the variant-at-root form over file extensions, and gives the three typed engines their dispatch point: match the Kind